                       <provenance type="found" when="1846">Discovered in 1846 by Cork antiquarians <persName>Windele</persName>, <persName>Abell</persName>, and <persName>Hawkes</persName> in a souterrain <idno type="SMR">(CO085-067002-)</idno> in the SW quadrant of a ringfort <idno type="SMR">(CO085-067001-)</idno>, with five other ogham stones: I-COR-046, I-COR-047, I-COR-048, I-COR-050 and I-COR-051. In 1849 Windele removed five of the stones, including this one, to his own residence (Blair's Castle, Cork) but they were later moved to the museum of the Royal Irish Academy (Brash 1879, 140; Macalister 1945, 92-93). 
                        </provenance>
